data.title: Nxera Pharma reports Q3 and 9-month results for 2025; headquartered in Tokyo, Japan, with updates on operational activities.
data.description: On 31 October 2025, Nxera Pharma, a pharmaceutical company based in Tokyo, Japan and Cambridge, UK, released an update on its operational activities. The Company, listed on the Tokyo Stock Exchange (TSE: 4565), disclosed its consolidated financial results for the third quarter and the nine months concluding on 30 September 2025. Further details can be accessed through the complete report available on their website.

data.title: Nxera Pharma received manufacturing approval amendment for QUVIVIQ® 25 and 50mg in Asia, originally launched in Japan for chronic insomnia. Taiwan approval pending, Phase 3 trials in S. Korea.
data.description: On October 31, 2025, Nxera Pharma Co., Ltd. shared that its subsidiary, Nxera Pharma Japan Co., Ltd., obtained a manufacturing approval partial amendment for QUVIVIQ® (daridorexant) 25 and 50 mg in Japan. Daridorexant, the active ingredient of QUVIVIQ®, was introduced in Japan as a treatment for chronic insomnia in December 2024. The Company is currently waiting for regulatory approval in Taiwan and is in the Phase 3 trial stage in South Korea. Nxera Pharma Co., Ltd. is listed on the Tokyo Stock Exchange under the ticker symbol 4565.

data.title: Strong performance in first 9 months of 2025, with net profit of DKK 16.7 billion due to good customer activity and credit quality.
data.description: Positive customer engagement and robust credit quality contributed to successful performance in the initial three quarters of 2025, resulting in a net profit of DKK 16.7 billion.

data.title: Marimekko's Q3 net sales up 8% to EUR 50.8M & operating profit at EUR 12.5M. Jan-Sep net sales at EUR 134.8M. Full story: Benzinga.com.
data.description: Marimekko Corporation's interim report for January to September 2025 reveals positive growth in net sales and operating profit. In the third quarter, net sales increased by 8% to EUR 50.8 million, with operating profit reaching EUR 12.5 million. For the overall period, net sales grew by 5% to EUR 134.8 million, and operating profit improved to EUR 23.1 million. International sales saw significant growth, with wholesale and retail sales both increasing. The company projects net sales for 2025 to surpass the previous year, targeting a 16-19% operating profit margin. However, global trade policy shifts and market uncertainties pose risks. Key figures include a 8% growth in international sales for Q3 2025 and a 12% increase in EBITDA. Operating profit margin for Q3 2025 was at 24.6%, higher than the previous year. Further details available on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Data breach at Conduent Business Services, LLC exposes 10.5 million records; under investigation.
data.description: A law firm based in San Francisco, Schubert Jonckheer & Kolbe LLP, is currently looking into a data breach incident that resulted in the unauthorized exposure of confidential data belonging to 10,515,849 individuals associated with clients of Conduent Business Services, LLC. The breach is being investigated following the incident, which occurred in New Jersey.

data.title: Aker Solutions had strong 3Q results in 2025, with revenues expected to surpass NOK 60 billion.
data.description: Norwegian company Aker Solutions showed robust growth and profitable margins in the third quarter of 2025. Significant progress was achieved in various projects during this period, contributing to the company's positive performance. Anticipated revenues for 2025 are now projected to surpass NOK 60 billion, reflecting the company's strong position in the market. This development signifies a promising outlook for Aker Solutions in the coming months.

data.description: Beijing, October 31, 2025 - Realsee, a company specializing in digital space solutions, has revealed a new strategic partnership with Linkhome AI Inc., a subsidiary of Linkhome Holdings Inc., a prominent real estate technology firm driven by artificial intelligence. This collaboration marks a significant step forward in the industry as two innovative leaders join forces.

data.title: Partnering for green steel production at scale, ROTOBOOST and Baowu, the world's largest steelmaker, collaborate under the BF-MOST Joint Innovation Call.
data.description: In Shanghai on October 31, 2025, ROTOBOOST of Finland and Baowu Clean Energy of China were revealed as the selected participants in the Business Finland (BF) – Ministry of Science and Technology of China (MOST) Joint Innovation Call. This initiative, backed by the governments of both countries, aims to foster collaboration between Finnish and Chinese entities.
